class MarketOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Market order.

A Market order is an order to BUY (or SELL) at the market bid or offer price. A market order may increase the likelihood of a fill and the speed of execution, but unlike the Limit order - a Market order provides no price protection and may fill at a price far lower/higher than the top of book bid/ask.

  • A Market-On-Open (MOO) order can be represented using a time in force of AT_THE_OPEN .

  • A Market-On-Close (MOC) order can be represented using a time in force of AT_THE_CLOSE .

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , DAY , AT_THE_OPEN , AT_THE_CLOSE }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If order_side is NO_ORDER_SIDE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is GTD .

class LimitOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , Price price , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , uint64_t expire_time_ns=0 , bool post_only=False , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , Quantity display_qty=None , TriggerType emulation_trigger=TriggerType.NO_TRIGGER , InstrumentId trigger_instrument_id=None , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Limit order.

A Limit order is an order to BUY (or SELL) at a specified price or better. The Limit order ensures that if the order fills, it will not fill at a price less favorable than your limit price, but it does not guarantee a fill.

  • A Limit-On-Open (LOO) order can be represented using a time in force of AT_THE_OPEN .

  • A Limit-On-Close (LOC) order can be represented using a time in force of AT_THE_CLOSE .

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order limit price.

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY , AT_THE_OPEN , AT_THE_CLOSE }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • post_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order will only provide liquidity (make a market).

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • display_qty ( Quantity , optional ) ‚Äì The quantity of the order to display on the public book (iceberg).

  • emulation_trigger (EmulationTrigger, default NO_TRIGGER ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger for the order.

  • trigger_instrument_id ( InstrumentId , optional ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger instrument ID for the order (if None then will be the instrument_id ).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If order_side is NO_ORDER_SIDE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is GTD and expire_time_ns <= UNIX epoch.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If display_qty is negative (< 0) or greater than quantity .

References

https://www.interactivebrokers.com/en/trading/orders/limit.php

class StopMarketOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , Price trigger_price , TriggerType trigger_type , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , uint64_t expire_time_ns=0 , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , TriggerType emulation_trigger=TriggerType.NO_TRIGGER , InstrumentId trigger_instrument_id=None , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Stop-Market conditional order.

A Stop-Market order is an instruction to submit a BUY (or SELL) market order if and when the specified stop trigger price is attained or penetrated. A Stop-Market order is not guaranteed a specific execution price and may execute significantly away from its stop price.

A SELL Stop-Market order is always placed below the current market price, and is typically used to limit a loss or protect a profit on a long position.

A BUY Stop-Market order is always placed above the current market price, and is typically used to limit a loss or protect a profit on a short position.

class StopLimitOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , Price price , Price trigger_price , TriggerType trigger_type , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , uint64_t expire_time_ns=0 , bool post_only=False , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , Quantity display_qty=None , TriggerType emulation_trigger=TriggerType.NO_TRIGGER , InstrumentId trigger_instrument_id=None , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Stop-Limit conditional order.

A Stop-Limit order is an instruction to submit a BUY (or SELL) limit order when the specified stop trigger price is attained or penetrated. The order has two basic components: the stop price and the limit price. When a trade has occurred at or through the stop price, the order becomes executable and enters the market as a limit order, which is an order to BUY (or SELL) at a specified price or better.

A Stop-Limit eliminates the price risk associated with a stop order where the execution price cannot be guaranteed, but exposes the trader to the risk that the order may never fill, even if the stop price is reached.

Parameters :

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order price (LIMIT).

  • trigger_price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order trigger price (STOP).

  • trigger_type ( TriggerType ) ‚Äì The order trigger type.

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • post_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order will only provide liquidity (once triggered).

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • display_qty ( Quantity , optional ) ‚Äì The quantity of the LIMIT order to display on the public book (iceberg).

  • emulation_trigger (EmulationTrigger, default NO_TRIGGER ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger for the order.

  • trigger_instrument_id ( InstrumentId , optional ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger instrument ID for the order (if None then will be the instrument_id ).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

class MarketToLimitOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , uint64_t expire_time_ns=0 , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , Quantity display_qty=None , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Market-To-Limit (MTL) order.

A Market-to-Limit (MTL) order is submitted as a market order to execute at the current best market price. If the order is only partially filled, the remainder of the order is canceled and re-submitted as a Limit order with the limit price equal to the price at which the filled portion of the order executed.

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • display_qty ( Quantity , optional ) ‚Äì The quantity of the limit order to display on the public book (iceberg).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

Bases: Order

Represents a Market-If-Touched (MIT) conditional order.

A Market-If-Touched (MIT) is an order to BUY (or SELL) an instrument below (or above) the market. This order is held in the system until the trigger price is touched, and is then submitted as a market order. An MIT order is similar to a Stop-Order, except that an MIT SELL order is placed above the current market price, and a stop SELL order is placed below.

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • trigger_price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order trigger price (STOP).

  • trigger_type ( TriggerType ) ‚Äì The order trigger type.

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • emulation_trigger (EmulationTrigger, default NO_TRIGGER ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger for the order.

  • trigger_instrument_id ( InstrumentId , optional ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger instrument ID for the order (if None then will be the instrument_id ).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If order_side is NO_ORDER_SIDE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If trigger_type is NO_TRIGGER .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is AT_THE_OPEN or AT_THE_CLOSE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is GTD and expire_time_ns <= UNIX epoch.

class LimitIfTouchedOrder ( TraderId trader_id , StrategyId strategy_id , InstrumentId instrument_id , ClientOrderId client_order_id , OrderSide order_side , Quantity quantity , Price price , Price trigger_price , TriggerType trigger_type , UUID4 init_id , uint64_t ts_init , TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC , uint64_t expire_time_ns=0 , bool post_only=False , bool reduce_only=False , bool quote_quantity=False , Quantity display_qty=None , TriggerType emulation_trigger=TriggerType.NO_TRIGGER , InstrumentId trigger_instrument_id=None , ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY , OrderListId order_list_id=None , list linked_order_ids=None , ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None , ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None , dict exec_algorithm_params=None , ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None , unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Limit-If-Touched (LIT) conditional order.

A Limit-If-Touched (LIT) is an order to BUY (or SELL) an instrument at a specified price or better, below (or above) the market. This order is held in the system until the trigger price is touched. A LIT order is similar to a Stop-Limit order, except that a LIT SELL order is placed above the current market price, and a Stop-Limit SELL order is placed below.

Using a LIT order helps to ensure that, if the order does execute, the order will not execute at a price less favorable than the limit price.

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order price (LIMIT).

  • trigger_price ( Price ) ‚Äì The order trigger price (STOP).

  • trigger_type ( TriggerType ) ‚Äì The order trigger type.

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • post_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order will only provide liquidity (once triggered).

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • display_qty ( Quantity , optional ) ‚Äì The quantity of the LIMIT order to display on the public book (iceberg).

  • emulation_trigger (EmulationTrigger, default NO_TRIGGER ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger for the order.

  • trigger_instrument_id ( InstrumentId , optional ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger instrument ID for the order (if None then will be the instrument_id ).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If order_side is NO_ORDER_SIDE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If trigger_type is NO_TRIGGER .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is AT_THE_OPEN or AT_THE_CLOSE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is GTD and expire_time_ns <= UNIX epoch.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If display_qty is negative (< 0) or greater than quantity .

class TrailingStopLimitOrder ( TraderId trader_id, StrategyId strategy_id, InstrumentId instrument_id, ClientOrderId client_order_id, OrderSide order_side, Quantity quantity, Price price: Optional[Price], Price trigger_price: Optional[Price], TriggerType trigger_type, limit_offset: Decimal, trailing_offset: Decimal, TrailingOffsetType trailing_offset_type, UUID4 init_id, uint64_t ts_init, TimeInForce time_in_force=TimeInForce.GTC, uint64_t expire_time_ns=0, bool post_only=False, bool reduce_only=False, bool quote_quantity=False, Quantity display_qty=None, TriggerType emulation_trigger=TriggerType.NO_TRIGGER, InstrumentId trigger_instrument_id=None, ContingencyType contingency_type=ContingencyType.NO_CONTINGENCY, OrderListId order_list_id=None, list linked_order_ids=None, ClientOrderId parent_order_id=None, ExecAlgorithmId exec_algorithm_id=None, dict exec_algorithm_params=None, ClientOrderId exec_spawn_id=None, unicode tags=None ) ¬∂

Bases: Order

Represents a Trailing-Stop-Limit conditional order.

Parameters :

  • trader_id ( TraderId ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the order.

  • strategy_id ( StrategyId ) ‚Äì The strategy ID associated with the order.

  • instrument_id ( InstrumentId ) ‚Äì The order instrument ID.

  • client_order_id ( ClientOrderId ) ‚Äì The client order ID.

  • order_side (OrderSide { BUY , SELL }) ‚Äì The order side.

  • quantity ( Quantity ) ‚Äì The order quantity (> 0).

  • price (Price, optional with no default so None must be passed explicitly) ‚Äì The order price (LIMIT). If None then will typically default to the delta of market price and limit_offset .

  • trigger_price (Price, optional with no default so None must be passed explicitly) ‚Äì The order trigger price (STOP). If None then will typically default to the delta of market price and trailing_offset .

  • trigger_type ( TriggerType ) ‚Äì The order trigger type.

  • limit_offset ( Decimal ) ‚Äì The trailing offset for the order price (LIMIT).

  • trailing_offset ( Decimal ) ‚Äì The trailing offset for the order trigger price (STOP).

  • trailing_offset_type ( TrailingOffsetType ) ‚Äì The order trailing offset type.

  • init_id ( UUID4 ) ‚Äì The order initialization event ID.

  • ts_init ( uint64_t ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the object was initialized.

  • time_in_force (TimeInForce { GTC , IOC , FOK , GTD , DAY }, default GTC ) ‚Äì The order time in force.

  • expire_time_ns ( uint64_t , default 0 ( no expiry ) ) ‚Äì The UNIX timestamp (nanoseconds) when the order will expire.

  • post_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order will only provide liquidity (once triggered).

  • reduce_only ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the LIMIT order carries the ‚Äòreduce-only‚Äô execution instruction.

  • quote_quantity ( bool , default False ) ‚Äì If the order quantity is denominated in the quote currency.

  • display_qty ( Quantity , optional ) ‚Äì The quantity of the LIMIT order to display on the public book (iceberg).

  • emulation_trigger (TriggerType, default NO_TRIGGER ) ‚Äì The order emulation trigger.

  • trigger_instrument_id ( InstrumentId , optional ) ‚Äì The emulation trigger instrument ID for the order (if None then will be the instrument_id ).

  • contingency_type (ContingencyType, default NO_CONTINGENCY ) ‚Äì The order contingency type.

  • order_list_id ( OrderListId , optional ) ‚Äì The order list ID associated with the order.

  • linked_order_ids ( list [ ClientOrderId ] , optional ) ‚Äì The order linked client order ID(s).

  • parent_order_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The order parent client order ID.

  • exec_algorithm_id ( ExecAlgorithmId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm ID for the order.

  • exec_algorithm_params ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm parameters for the order.

  • exec_spawn_id ( ClientOrderId , optional ) ‚Äì The execution algorithm spawning primary client order ID.

  • tags ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom user tags for the order. These are optional and can contain any arbitrary delimiter if required.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If order_side is NO_ORDER_SIDE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If quantity is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If trigger_type is NO_TRIGGER .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If trailing_offset_type is NO_TRAILING_OFFSET .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is AT_THE_OPEN or AT_THE_CLOSE .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If time_in_force is GTD and expire_time_ns <= UNIX epoch.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If display_qty is negative (< 0) or greater than quantity .

Return whether the order is closed.

An order is considered closed when its status can no longer change. The possible statuses of closed orders include;

  • DENIED

  • REJECTED

  • CANCELED

  • EXPIRED

  • FILLED

Returns :

bool

Returns :

is_inflight ¬∂

Return whether the order is in-flight (order request sent to the trading venue).

An order is considered in-flight when its status is any of;

  • SUBMITTED

  • PENDING_UPDATE

  • PENDING_CANCEL

Returns :

bool

Warning

An emulated order is never considered in-flight.

is_open ¬∂

Return whether the order is open at the trading venue.

An order is considered open when its status is any of;

  • ACCEPTED

  • TRIGGERED

  • PENDING_UPDATE

  • PENDING_CANCEL

  • PARTIALLY_FILLED

Returns :

bool

Warning

An emulated order is never considered open.
